(3637, 583, 'Image-meta', 'a:10:{i:0;a:3:{s:5:"title";s:0:"";s:11:"description";s:179:"Two hours of dirt road from Syafrubesi, Gatlang is the first stop on the Tamang Heritage Trail. It is known for its majority Tamang community living in a tight-knit web of houses.";s:5:"image";s:3:"579";}i:1;a:3:{s:5:"title";s:42:"Art Works! Sangai Khelaun, Gatlang, Rasuwa";s:11:"description";s:118:"Photo by: Merit Maharjan, houses from with stone laid walls, carved wooden faces, and roofs made of wooden shingles.  ";s:5:"image";s:3:"580";}i:2;a:3:{s:5:"title";s:42:"Art Works! Sangai Khelaun, Gatlang, Rasuwa";s:11:"description";s:229:"The April earthquake and its aftershocks destroyed all he homes from Gatlang.  Over five hundred households have been displaced.  With a few exceptions, most people are living in scattered tents on the outskirts of the village.  ";s:5:"image";s:3:"581";}i:3;a:3:{s:5:"title";s:42:"Art Works! Sangai Khelaun, Gatlang, Rasuwa";s:11:"description";s:51:"People from Gatlang engage in substantial farming. ";s:5:"image";s:3:"584";}i:4;a:3:{s:5:"title";s:0:"";s:11:"description";s:90:"The harvested beans. The beans from Gatlang is very famous for its taste and for the Daal.";s:5:"image";s:3:"589";}i:5;a:3:{s:5:"title";s:0:"";s:11:"description";s:27:"Beans ready for harvesting.";s:5:"image";s:3:"590";}i:6;a:3:{s:5:"title";s:0:"";s:11:"description";s:281:"Pemba Dezi, local residents and weaver, weaving a cloth to make Bakhu for his husband for this year winter season. The yarns are self-made which are made from sheep wool. They also dyed the yarn themselves. Most of women can weave and make the cloth for their husband and children.";s:5:"image";s:3:"591";}i:7;a:3:{s:5:"title";s:0:"";s:11:"description";s:62:"Husband of Temba Dezi wearing a Bakhu made and weave by Temba.";s:5:"image";s:3:"592";}i:8;a:3:{s:5:"title";s:0:"";s:11:"description";s:51:"Morning assembly at Nepal Rastriya Secondary School";s:5:"image";s:3:"593";}i:9;a:3:{s:5:"title";s:0:"";s:11:"description";s:75:"Morning meeting with Nepal Ratriya Secondary School principle and teachers.";s:5:"image";s:3:"594";}}'),
