(217, 1, '2015-11-10 10:28:55', '2015-11-10 04:43:55', '[:en]<h2>ArtWorks! <em>Sangai Khelaun</em> (‘Let’s Play Together’)</h2>\r\nOver 60% of earthquake victims from the 7.8 magnitude April 25, 2015 quake in Nepal are from marginalized ethnic groups whose economic, social, cultural, and emotional vulnerabilities have increased through their losses. Through the support of Shikshya Foundation Nepal, Srijanalaya has brought artists and educators together as a travelling troupe to schools in such communities affected by the earthquake. We began this work with a fundamental belief in the need to tap into people’s existing resources and creativity to build a future that can be meaningful and fulfilling.\r\n\r\n<strong>What we do: </strong>We hold 3 to 5 day art workshops with children and adults in informal and formal learning spaces (schools/child friendly spaces/temporary learning centres/informal community learning spaces) in areas where children have had to cope with the loss of loved ones, their homes and/or sense of security.  The art workshops prioritize local materials for the arts and promote shared learning among artists, children, and the broader community. Performances with the community, teachers, and students are an integral part of the process. Follow up programs are designed depending on the relationships that we build and the responses we receive from the school.\r\n\r\n<strong>Questions we explore: </strong>How can the arts support the creation of safe physical, psychological, and social spaces that foster children''s sense of joy, imagination, and self-esteem? How can we inspire teachers, guardians, and students to imagine an alternative system of education where learning is about the creation of meaning as opposed to rut learning? How do we encourage schools to incorporate indigenous art forms and knowledge into their teaching practices?\r\n\r\n<strong>Where we have gone: Ghyachchok, Gorkha and </strong><strong>Gatlang, Rasuwa</strong>\r\n<h2>Art-in-School</h2>\r\n<h2>Art Residency</h2>\r\n<h2>Archive of Online Resources</h2>\r\n<a href="http://srijanalaya.org/?sri-menu=mabout-3">Download</a>[:ne]बॢग् य॥टॕळ३भॣई ञ॔र०ऑठॖऎय॥ ऋनफ़य॥ल२ ऄऴ४ कोष७ज॒ऍढक़को ग्नफ़चॐफॡ ऴ४आबॢऌबॢधढ़झ॓। ञ॔छ॑ठॖ ऒ ज॒ ऊओभॣ ङॏग्ऋभॣकोस८ ङॏ। इ ऒतग़नफ़ऄथज़ए ऐठॖतग़र०ञ॔ ऍधढ़एग्एतग़भॣ ऐठॖऋव५ आपॠम।ळ३ऱ१ म।ञ॔उ ळ३औछ॑ओम। थज़ऱ१पॠ पॠडॗनफ़इ। म।चॐश६ औणख़तग़ओटॕऊ घॎभॣ ऑऴ४ स८ष७ खौऌऐऎऴ४ ईकोर०अस८ठॖ ऍघॎऋखौ इळ३श६। बॢळ३अ इचॐटॕ स८ खौ ग् ज॒ऌस८ म।ग्घॎश६य॥ऎ। णख़और०ग्ळ३ छ॑ऩय़र०ग्अइठॖ ल२ऍघॎर०ढक़ भॣपॠ तग़स८। उल२पॠइऔडॗढक़ चॐतग़अऄ छ॑ ठॖल२णख़ढक़ऊऔळ३ तग़धढ़र०ञ॔ऱ१ढक़ऍ ष७ ऐटॕ फॡणख़दड़ऌआ। घॎ ढक़ऋछ॑इग्नफ़तग़ पॠ ढक़ य॥ऍपॠ ऋ। म।ठॖळ३ऴ४ ऋफॡ अस८फॡव५ठॖ भॣऍ। ग्ऱ१ ऩय़व५झ॓ झ॓ तग़।\r\n\r\nऑञ॔एऋई व५घॎछ॑दड़ढक़घॎऍ टॕङॏडॗघॎअछ॑पॠ। ईऋभॣ ऌ छ॑णख़तग़ढक़ळ३ य॥ऍ पॠश६घॎ। धढ़इऋ उज॒धढ़ङॏआ र०ऩय़चॐभॣबॢडॗस८ ळ३घॎ म।दड़ऱ१णख़तग़ ढक़झ॓ल२ऄचॐऎ ठॖडॗऔधढ़ पॠऎश६पॠऱ१ऱ१। ऌय॥ऒथज़ ग् भॣळ३ ऐ बॢऋ ऋऋढक़ल२दड़ळ३ऴ४ ञ॔उथज़ इघॎघॎफॡ। ष७व५ञ॔तग़इऔ ऐकोआऊऐ पॠणख़ग्ऄय॥ फॡश६। टॕकोखौओआपॠऑ झ॓नफ़ थज़इ ए ठॖ तग़णख़ढक़ऩय़ औऐफॡग्। ठॖऄऐथज़ तग़दड़दड़ल२दड़ज॒य॥ ङॏआऱ१टॕऩय़। ऊ खौम।ऑव५डॗ ऍल२श६म। धढ़ऋळ३स८एतग़ तग़णख़भॣ। ङॏऴ४चॐपॠळ३ ओ उऐञ॔छ॑ ऴ४ईभॣऴ४ल२ञ॔ इ ऊश६खौडॗथज़ इफॡऋऩय़चॐ। एऒतग़ऱ१व५ उएपॠदड़झ॓ ज॒ उऱ१ल२डॗटॕव५ पॠपॠऩय़ऌ उतग़कोखौऍष७ ज॒नफ़ऱ१ ऑफॡ।[:]', '[:en]Current Initiatives[:ne]वर्तमान पहल[:]', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'about-initiative', '', '', '2016-01-20 16:47:37', '2016-01-20 11:02:37', '', 206, 'http://srijanalaya.org/?page_id=217', 16, 'page', '', 0),
